20the%20threat%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-lawmakers-briefed-russia-trying-put-nuclear-weapon-space-reports-2024-2%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia%20developing%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20deployed%20against%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatellites%20are%20pivotal%20for%20transmitting%20information%20ranging%20from%20cellphone%20data%20to%20military%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanetta%20made%20some%20efforts%20to%20flesh%20out%20how%20such%20a%20system%20could%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20spoke%20in%20hypothetical%20terms%2C%20and%20didn't%20claim%20to%20have%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Russia%20could%20blind%20our%20ability%20to%20be%20able%20to%20gather%20that%20kind%20of%20information%2C%20make%20no%20mistake%20about%20it%2C%20that%20would%20be%20an%20act%20of%20war%20because%20it%20would%20threaten%20our%20national%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Panetta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20US%20was%20likely%20developing%20a%20similar%20capacity%20to%20target%20satellites%2C%20and%20also%20to%20defend%20its%20own%20satellites%20from%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I'm%20sure%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20is%20developing%20the%20ability%20not%20only%20to%20track%20what%20the%20Russians%20are%20doing%20and%20determine%20whether%20or%20not%20they're%20going%20to%20try%20to%20deploy%20something%20like%20this%20but%20also%20how%20they%20defend%20against%20it%20if%20it%20should%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Republican%20Rep.%20Michael%20Turner%20of%20Ohio%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20House%20Intelligence%20Committee%2C%20called%20on%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20declassify%20information%20on%20the%20threat%2C%20which%20he%20did%20not%20describe%20in%20any%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EABC%20News%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F14%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fintelligence-russia-nuclear.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20later%20reported%20that%20the%20threat%20was%20the%20development%20by%20Russia%20of%20a%20nuclear%20space%20weapon%2C%20which%2C%20according%20to%20the%20reports%2C%20could%20disable%20civilian%20communication%2C%20GPS%2C%20surveillance%20from%20space%2C%20as%20well%20as%20military%20command%20and%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20reports%20described%20it%20differently%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fshow%2Fnational-security-warning-reportedly-involves-russian-space-weapon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPBS%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20sources%20saying%20the%20satellite%20would%20be%20powered%20by%20a%20nuclear%20reactor%20but%20was%20not%20itself%20a%20nuclear%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20US%20official%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20the%20US%20does%20not%20currently%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20counter%20the%20threat%20but%20that%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20Russian%20weapon%20did%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20imminent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20the%20weapon%20would%20likely%20breach%20the%201967%20Outer%20Space%20Treaty%20between%20the%20US%20and%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20(later%20Russia)%20and%20many%20other%20nations.%20The%20treaty%20bans%20signatory%20nations%20from%20putting%20nuclear%20weapons%20in%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecurity%20experts%20have%20long%20believed%20that%20if%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20were%20to%20go%20to%20war%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Finternational%2F2024%2F01%2F31%2Famerica-china-and-russia-are-locked-in-a-new-struggle-over-space%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20attacks%20to%20disable%20satellites%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20among%20the%20first%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reports%20come%20as%20House%20Republicans%20continued%20their%20opposition%20to%20a%20bill%20that%20includes%20%2466%20billion%20in%20aid%20to%20Ukrai