%2F02%2F70x70%2Fskynews-beef-rice-lab-grown-meat_6456327.jpg%3F20240215103555%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20in%20South%20Korea%20have%20grown%20beef%20cells%20inside%20grains%20of%20rice%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20create%20food%20that%20is%20cheaper%20and%20more%20eco-friendly%20than%20real%20cuts%20of%20meat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Part%20of%20Secret%20Ballot'%3A%20How%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Backed%20Electoral%20Bonds%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F10170626%2Fsyed-hussaini-HlLno-CSbq8-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20February%2015%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Epronounced%20electoral%20bonds%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20in%202018%20and%20allowed%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%20To%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20heard%20pleas%20against%20the%20bonds%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20spoke%20of%20its%20justification%20for%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20one%20which%20the%20court%20has%20now%20held%20as%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20written%20submission%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20said%20that%20citizens%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20must%20be%20balanced%20with%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy%20while%20donating%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20maintained%20that%20the%20citizens%20did%20not%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgeneral%20right%20to%20know%20regarding%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%98right%20to%20know%E2%80%99%20itself%20is%20not%20a%20general%20right%20available%20to%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20argued%20against%20the%20court%20examining%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinfluence%20of%20contributions%20by%20companies%20to%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20issue%20of%20democratic%20significance%20that%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cbest%20left%20to%20the%20legislature.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Union%20also%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20exercise%20judicial%20restraint%20citing%20the%20legislation%E2%80%99s%20connection%20to%20economic%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20contended%20that%20the%20right%20of%20a%20buyer%20to%20purchase%20electoral%20bonds%20without%20having%20to%20disclose%20their%20political%20preferences%20ensured%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy.%20The%20Union%20also%20told%20the%20court%20that%20%E2%80%9Canonymous%20political%20donations%E2%80%9D%20were%20a%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20concept%20of%20secret%20ballot%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdonating%20money%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20party%20is%20a%20form%20of%20political%20self-expression%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20privacy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20Union%20did%20not%20distinguish%20between%20individuals%20and%20corporations%20while%20arguing%20for%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20citizens%20while%20buying%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Are%20Illegal%20Now.%20But%20Who%20Benefitted%20for%20the%206%2B%20Years%20They%20Lasted%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fact%20that%20one%20party%20has%20received%20more%20support%20through%20donations%20than%20other%20parties%20cannot%20in%20itself%20be%20the%20legal%20grounds%20to%20challenge%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20government%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20been%20the%20net%20gainer%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20Of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3Ethe%20BJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Congress%20has%20received%20just%209.5%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20at%20Rs%201%2C135%20crore.%20The%20Trinamool%20Congress%20has%20received%20Rs%201%2C096%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20this%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20while%20rejecting%20the%20Union%E2%80%99s%20argument%20in%20favour%20of%20exercising%20judicial%20restraint%20on%20account%20of%20the%20legislation%20being%20a%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Ceconomic%20policy%E2%80%9D%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20does%20not%20rely%20on%20ipse%20dixit%20%5Bassertion%5D%20of%20the%20government%2C%20that%20a%20legislation%20is%20an%20economic%20legislation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20amendment%20to%20Section%2031%20of%20the%20RBI%20Act%20can%20be%20classified%20as%20a%20financial%20provision%E2%80%A6%20However%2C%20any%20resemblance%20to%20an%20economic%20policy%20ends%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20amendment%20in%20question%20fall%20under%20the%20following%20two%20heads%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Non-disclosure%20of%20information%20on%20electoral%20financing%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20Provisions%20permitting%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20both%20accounts%2C%20the%20legislation%20relates%20to%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%20the%20court%20said%20as%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Edeclared%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20as%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20verdict%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993917000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F10170626%2Fsyed-hussaini-HlLno-CSbq8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20had%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdonating%20money%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20party%20is%20a%20form%20of%20political%20self-expression%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20privacy%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BGuy%20Who%20Was%20Hosting%20Was%20Mean%26quot%3B%3A%20SRK%20On%20Turning%20Down%20Slumdog%20Millionaire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fvalentine-s-day-2024-whirlwind-of-romance-featuring-shah-rukh-khan-and-kajol-5055487%5C%22%20data-mce-href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fvalentine-s-day-2024-whirlwind-of-romance-featuring-shah-rukh-khan-and-kajol-5055487%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShah%20Rukh%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20recently%20disclosed%20that%20he%20was%20offered%20a%20role%20in%20the%20Oscar-winning%20film%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESlumdog%20Millionaire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20actor%20revealed%20his%20reasons%20for%20declining%20the%20role%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EKaun%20Banega%20Crorepati%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0show%20host%20in%20the%20movie.%20It%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%20was%20hosting%20the%20same%20show%20for%20a%20television%20channel%20during%20that%20time%20frame.%20During%20the%20World%20Government%20Summit%202024%20in%20Dubai%2C%20SRK%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CYes%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESlumdog%20%5BMillionaire%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0was%20there%2C%20now%20that%20you%20mention%20it.%20And%20I%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20with%20Mr.%20Boyle%20(Danny%20Boyle).%20He's%20very%20sweet.%20But%20I%20was%20doing%C2%A0%3Cem%3EKaun%20Banega%20Crorepati%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0on%20television%2C%20successfully%20at%20that%20time.%20And%20I%20just%20felt%20in%20the%20story%20that%20was%20being%20told%2C%20the%20guy%20who%20was%20hosting%20was%20very%20mean%2C%20in%20the%20story%20that%20was%20being%20told.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20why%20he%20said%20no%20to%20the%20role%20that%20ultimately%20landed%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftom-cruise-shares-video-with-snippets-of-all-mission-impossible-movies-co-star-anil-kapoor-reacted-like-this-5041634%5C%22%20data-mce-href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftom-cruise-shares-video-with-snippets-of-all-mission-impossible-movies-co-star-anil-kapoor-reacted-like-this-5041634%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnil%20Kapoor%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0SRK%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20cheating%20and%20being%20dishonest%20as%20the%20host%20(in%20the%20movie).%20So%20I%20just%20found%20that%20it's%20very%20strange%20that%20I'm%20being%20a%20host%20(on%3Cem%3E%C2%A0KBC%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20I'm%20cheating%20in%20the%20film.%20So%20I%20explained%20to%20Mr%20Boyle%20(Danny%20Boyle)%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20like%20to%20do%20it%2C%20please%2C%20and%20there%20are%20way%20better%20actors%20than%20me.%20And%20I%20think%20Mr%20Anil%20Kapoor%20did%20it%20and%20he%20was%20fantastic%20as%20the%20host.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20Summit%2C%20King%20Khan%20also%20discussed%20how%20he%20has%20never%20been%20offered%20any%20substantial%20crossover%20projects%20from%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fid-love-to-to-play-a-bond-villain-says-srk-at-world-government-summit-5057807%5C%22%20data-mce-href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fid-love-to-to-play-a-bond-villain-says-srk-at-world-government-summit-5057807%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHollywood%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20megastar%20stated%2C%20%26quot%3BI've%20said%20this%20honestly%2C%20but%20nobody%20believes%20me.%20Nobody%20has%20offered%20me%20any%20crossover%20work%20of%20substance.%20I%20may%20have%20had%20conversations%20with%20people.%20I%20know%20lots%20of%20lovely%20people%20from%20the%20West%2C%20from%20the%20English%20film%20industry%2C%20from%20the%20American%20film%20industry%2C%20but%20nobody%20has%20offered%20me%20any%20work.%20I%20hear%20actors%20talk%20about%20wanting%20to%20cross%20over%2C%20but%20I%20still%20have%20to%20learn%20to%20deliver%20to%20the%20audience%20that%20likes%20me%2C%20instead%20of%20spreading%20myself%20too%20thin.%20So%2C%20really%2C%20I've%20never%20been%20offered%20a%20film%20in%20Hollywood%20or%20England.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20Rukh%20Khan%20was%20last%20seen%20in%20Rajkumar%20Hirani's%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDunki.%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20film%20is%20currently%20streaming%20on%20OTT%20platform%20Netflix.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fur0qv0io_kareena