%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15143525%2Fkevin-john-Q6FUBxz7HF8-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20to%20note%20in%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%20poll%20of%202024%20is%20a%20majority%20of%20those%20surveyed%20%E2%80%93%2064%25%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20substantial%20number%20of%20people%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20report%20that%20their%20economic%20situation%20has%20deteriorated%20or%20remained%20the%20same%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20seamless%20regime%20with%20a%20clear%20majority.%20Over%20one-third%2C%2035%25%2C%20say%20their%20situation%20has%20got%20worse%20relative%20to%20what%20what%20it%20was%20in%202014.%20This%20is%20one%20apiece%20with%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20consumer%20confidence%20surveys%2C%20which%20have%20been%20noting%20the%20despondent%20mood%20amongst%20those%20surveyed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Fexplainspeaking-consumer-sentiments-improving-but-still-stuck-in-pessimism-9160505%2F%5C%22%3Ethrough%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20second%20term%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20starting%20from%202019%2C%20well%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India%20Today%20Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%20poll%2C%20which%20brings%20out%20the%20economic%20discontent%20and%20restlessness%20vividly%2C%20was%20conducted%20by%20CVoter.%20The%20survey%20has%2035%2C801%20respondents%2C%20reached%20out%20through%20computer%20assisted%20telephone%20interviews%20(CATI)%20between%20December%2015%2C%202023%20and%20January%2028%2C%202024%2C%20with%20the%20interviews%20covering%20all%20Lok%20Sabha%20segments%20across%20all%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D%3A%2071%25%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20unemployment%2C%2071%25%20say%20the%20situation%20is%20either%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20serious%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D.%20A%20whopping%2054%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20say%20the%20jobs%20situation%20is%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20serious%E2%80%9D.%20Objective%20data%20on%20the%20state%20of%20unemployment%2C%20despite%20government%20denials%2C%20has%20pointed%20to%20a%20sad%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20leading%20to%20even%20a%20controversial%20withholding%20of%20employment%20data%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20with%20the%20government%20agreeing%20to%20release%20the%20bad%20news%20only%20after%20the%202019%20general%20elections%20were%20over.%20This%20led%20to%20two%20resignations%20from%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20541px)%2085vw%2C%20541px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22541%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201104w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x270.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x920.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697299%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22487%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quality%20of%20jobs%20has%20also%20been%20a%20point%20of%20distress%2C%20with%20formal%20employment%20going%20down.%20State%20jobs%20or%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ebhartis%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20postponed%20for%20years%20on%20end%20with%20an%20entire%20generation%20preparing%20for%20%E2%80%98competitive%20examinations%E2%80%99%20feeling%20left%20out%20and%20out%20of%20a%20job.%20The%20Armed%20Forces%20deciding%20to%20move%20towards%20an%20%E2%80%98Agniveer%E2%80%99%20model%20of%20hiring%20soldiers%2C%20or%20short-term%20contract%20soldiering%20wholly%20replacing%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20soldier%20as%20a%20job%20providing%20respect%2C%20regular%20income%20and%20purpose%20has%20hit%20avenues%20for%20jobs%20for%20youngsters%2C%20with%20consequences%20in%20a%20demographic%20where%20the%20median%20age%20in%20India%20is%20around%2030%20years.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F254469%2Fmedian-age-of-the-population-in-india%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520median%2520age%2520in%2520India%2C50.4%2520years%2520old%2520by%25202100.%5C%22%3EStatista%2C%20(as%20there%20has%20been%20no%20Census%20since%202011%3C%2Fa%3E)%20says%20it%20was%C2%A0a%20median%20of%2032.4%20years%20old%C2%A0in%202020%2C%20meaning%20that%20half%20the%20population%20is%20older%20than%20that%2C%20and%20the%20other%20half%20younger.%20Lower%20median%20ages%20need%20more%20job%20making.%20This%20figure%20was%20lowest%20in%201970%2C%20at%2017.3%20years%2C%20by%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CCurrent%20Household%20Expenses%E2%80%9D%20out%20of%20whack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCurrent%20household%20expenses%20are%20difficult%20to%20manage%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20this%20worries%2062%25%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20If%20you%20add%20those%20who%20worry%20about%20raised%20expenses%20but%20still%20say%20it%20is%20manageable%20(33%25)%2C%20this%20makes%20price%20rise%20a%20concern%20for%2095%25%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20This%20is%20the%20highest%20metric%20number%20logged%20for%20any%20question%20across%20the%20survey.%20A%20total%20of%2066%25%20say%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20their%20household%20incomes%20will%20rise.%2030%25%20feel%20it%20will%20deteriorate.%20Price%20inflation%20is%20the%20biggest%20failure%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20says%2026%25%20of%20the%20cohort%20surveyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20real%20numbers%20go%2C%20prices%20have%20been%20astronomical%2C%20and%20been%20well%20out%20of%20the%20RBI%20band%20of%20acceptable%20rates%20(between%204%20to%206%25)%20for%20some%20time%20now.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2FEconomy%2Fretail-inflation-eases-to-51-in-january-a-3-month-low%2Farticle67838256.ece%5C%22%3EIn%20latest%20figures%20in%20for%20January%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20food%20inflation%20is%20still%20high%2C%20at%208.3%25%20compared%20with%209.5%25%20in%20December%202023.%20The%20retail%20inflation%20is%20at%205.1%25%20in%20January%2C%20but%20has%20been%20hovering%20well%20above%20that%3B%20it%20was%205.7%25%20a%20month%20earlier.%20For%20urban%20India%2C%20food%20inflation%20is%20at%209%25.%20It%20was%20at%2010.4%25%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20521px)%2085vw%2C%20521px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22521%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x270.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x922.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697303%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20consumer%20confidence%20surveys%20bear%20out%20the%20anxiety%20among%20households%20over%20inflation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FPublicationsView.aspx%3Fid%3D22422%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20data%2C%20released%20on%20February%208%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20records%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmajority%20of%20survey%20participants%20expect%20a%20rise%20in%20price%20and%20inflationary%20pressures%20especially%20for%20food%20product%20category%20for%20the%20three%20months%20horizon%E2%80%9D.%20They%20say%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmedian%20inflation%20expectation%20for%20the%20three%20months%20ahead%20increased%20by%2010%20bps%20and%20stood%20at%209.2%20per%20cent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20Michael%20Debabrata%20Patra%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FBS_PressReleaseDisplay.aspx%3Fprid%3D56982%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20December%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cinflation%20remains%20highly%20vulnerable%20to%20food%20price%20spikes%2C%20as%20the%20spurt%20in%20momentum%20in%20daily%20data%20on%20key%20food%20items%20for%20the%20month%20of%20November%20and%20early%20December%20reveal%E2%80%9D.%20He%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%9Chouseholds%20are%20already%20wary%3A%20although%20they%20expect%20inflation%20to%20remain%20unchanged%20three%20months%20ahead%2C%20they%20are%20more%20unsure%20about%20this%20prognosis%20than%20they%20were%20two%20months%20ago.%20Over%20the%20year%20ahead%2C%20however%2C%20they%20are%20more%20sure%20than%20in%20the%20past%20that%20inflation%20will%20likely%20rise.%E2%80%9D%20Patra%20added%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cconsumers%20too%20reveal%20more%20pessimism%20about%20inflation%20a%20year%20ahead%20than%20when%20they%20were%20surveyed%20in%20September%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20say%20policies%20promote%20K-shaped%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20brings%20out%20the%20belief%20in%20the%20past%20ten%20years%20that%20economic%20policies%20are%20being%20drawn%20up%20to%20help%20big%20business.%20A%20majority%20of%20people%20surveyed%2C%2052%25%2C%20say%20so.%20Only%209%25%20think%20economic%20policies%20are%20benefitting%20farmers%2C%2011%25%20are%20of%20the%20view%20they%20support%20small%20business%20and%20only%208%25%20say%20they%20benefit%20the%20salaried%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20economic%20policies%20have%20ended%20up%20widening%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20poor%2C%20is%20the%20feeling%20of%20nearly%20half%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20About%2045%25%20feel%20that%20the%20gap%20has%20got%20wider.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20468px)%2085vw%2C%20468px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201056w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x290.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x991.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697331%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22453%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20analysis%20by%20India%20Ratings%20and%20Research%20for%20FY22%20and%20FY23%2C%20cited%20by%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cshows%20that%20wages%20for%20lower-income%20groups%2C%20comprising%20agricultural%20rural%20workers%20and%20unskilled%20workers%2C%20saw%20degrowth%20or%20negligible%20wage%20growth%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20In%20contrast%2C%20wages%20for%20corporates%2C%20representing%20the%20top%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20income%20bracket%2C%20increased%20by%20over%2010%20per%20cent%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years.%E2%80%9D%20The%20political%20landscape%20has%20been%20dominated%20by%20conversation%20over%20one%20business%20house%2C%20the%20Adani%20Group%E2%80%99s%20rapid%20growth%2C%20which%20continued%20also%20through%20the%20pandemic%2C%20far%20outstripping%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20in%20India%20and%20also%20growth%20of%20its%20peers%20in%20the%20business%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBig%20corporations%20as%20a%20group%20have%20benefitted%20from%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%2C%20says%20a%20look%20at%20taxes%20paid%20by%20them%2C%20as%20compared%20to%20what%20individuals%20pay.%20The%20government%20has%20been%20boasting%20about%20this.%20The%20government%20data%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fincome-tax-filers-more-than-double-to-77-8-million-in-10-years-govt-data-124012300845_1.html%5C%22%3Eas%20released%20by%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20CBDT%20says%20that%20the%20number%20of%20tax%20payers%20filing%20income%20tax%20returns%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%20to%207.78%20crore%20in%20the%20past%2010%20years.%20But%20this%20%E2%80%98data%E2%80%99%20conceals%20a%20bigger%20story%20that%20has%20implications%20on%20economic%20equality%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20only%20thrice%20since%20the%201990s%20that%20individuals%20have%20paid%20more%20than%20corporations%20as%20tax.%20The%20first%20was%20in%201991-92%2C%20then%20in%202020-21%20and%20now.%20Economic%20commentator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fprofits-for-corporates-taxes-for-individuals-2889682%5C%22%3EVivek%20Kaul%20cites%3C%2Fa%3E%20aggregate%20data%20of%2035%2C000%20companies%20sourced%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20(CMIE)%20which%20%E2%80%9Csuggests%20that%20profit-before-tax%20(PBT)%20of%20these%20companies%20went%20up%20144%25%20between%202018-19%20and%202021-22.%20Plus%2C%20the%20tax%20provisions%20went%20up%20just%2039%25%2C%20helping%20push%20up%20profit-after-tax%20(PAT)%20by%20244%25.%E2%80%9D%20The%20government%20had%20cut%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20in%20September%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20points%20out%20to%20how%20this%20inhibits%20private%20consumption%20growth%20in%202023-24%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%204.4%25%2C%20the%20slowest%20since%202002-03%2C%20except%20for%20the%20pandemic%20year.%20As%20private%20consumption%20forms%2057%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%2C%20the%20government%20could%20have%20slashed%20personal%20income%20tax%20rates%20in%20the%20interim%20budget%2C%20and%20encouraged%20people%20to%20spend%20more%20and%20drive%20consumption.%20But%20with%20the%20fall%20in%20corporate%20tax%20collections%2C%20it%20cannot%20do%20that.%20There%20is%20a%20huge%20and%20continued%20cess%20on%20petrol%20and%20fuel%2C%20despite%20a%20long%20span%20when%20oil%20prices%20were%20at%20record%20low%20levels%2C%20as%20none%20of%20the%20benefits%20were%20passed%20on%20to%20consumers.%20This%20is%20also%20an%20indirect%2C%20regressive%20tax%2C%20hurting%20those%20at%20the%20lower%20end%20of%20the%20income%20scale%20more%20acutely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20people%20have%20caught%20on%20to%20how%20policies%20are%20hurting%20those%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20scale%20disproportionately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%2C%20V.%20Anantha%20Nageswaran%20says%20today%20in%20a%20piece%20in%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20May%2C%20we%20will%20have%20learnt%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%20has%20grown%20by%20more%20than%207%25%20annually%20in%20real%20terms%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15143525%2Fkevin-john-Q6FUBxz7HF8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsurvey-finds-deep-economic-discontent-job-pessimism-52-say-modis-policies-favour-big-business%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20first%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%20poll%20of%202024%20rings%20alarm%20bells%20on%20deep%20economic%20anxiety.%20This%20is%20borne%20out%20by%20the%20latest%20RBI%20consumer%20confidence%20survey.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsurvey-finds-deep-economic-discontent-job-pessimism-52-say-modis-policies-favour-big-business